Summons & Pets

This section is still incomplete.

  • I do not have information on how pets' skill levels apply to their actual levels
  • Pet stats are not yet completed. They probably won't be done.

Some sorta random explanations:


The summons' base stats affect their resistances and such. They also affect a lot of things you can't change anyway because you can't give a summon a tattoo, but ok.


Learn level is the level the game considers the skill "learned" at even though you got your summon at a different level. It affects several things, including what level recharge starts to weaken at or how well debuffs land.


Lastly, I've got to say this: NCSoft is very, very lazy when it comes to making summon stats. It doesn't really seem like they wanted summoners to be "hard" to level with because of crappy summon stats. No, they were just too lazy to change the summon stats any more than they had to.

All summons listed here have the following base stats unless otherwise noted:

  • STR 40
  • CON 43
  • DEX 30
  • INT 21
  • WIT 20
  • MEN 25
  • Critical 40*
  • Atk. Spd. 278.3
  • Casting Spd. 333

* Summon Critical operates differently than PC Critical.


This is what players have said about it:

  • With base Critical of 40
    • Unbuffed:40
    • Focus 1-3: 50
    • Song of Hunter: 80
    • Focus+Song of Hunter: 100
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Chant of Victory: 110
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Final Servitor: 110
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Blessing of Queen: 110

  • With base Critical of 80
    • Unbuffed: 80
    • Focus: 110
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Chant of Victory: 220
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Final Servitor: 220
    • Focus+Song of Hunter+Blessing of Queen: 220
